<li>West, Douglas B. (2001). <i>Introduction to Graph Theory</i> (2ed). Upper Saddle River: Prentice Hall. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0130144002" class="internal">ISBN 0-13-014400-2</a>. [<i>Tons of illustrations, references, and exercises. The most complete introductory guide to the subject.</i>]</li>
<li><cite id="Reference-Mathworld-Graph"><a href="/wiki/Eric_W._Weisstein" title="Eric W. Weisstein">Eric W. Weisstein</a>, <i><a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Graph.html" class="external text" title="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Graph.html" rel="nofollow">Graph</a></i> at <a href="/wiki/MathWorld" title="MathWorld">MathWorld</a>.</cite></li>
<li>Zaslavsky, Thomas. Glossary of signed and gain graphs and allied areas. <i>Electronic Journal of Combinatorics</i>, Dynamic Surveys in Combinatorics, # DS 8. <a href="http://www.combinatorics.org/Surveys/" class="external free" title="http://www.combinatorics.org/Surveys/" rel="nofollow">http://www.combinatorics.org/Surveys/</a></li>
</ul>


